<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="58" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
Based on the description and the figures by 
<bibRefCitation author="Emeljanov, AF" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" pagination="127 - 140" title="New Cixiidae (Hemiptera, Auchenorrhycha) from the Ryukyus, Japan." volume="13" year="2007">Emeljanov and Hayashi (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, this species can be distinguished from the other species of the genus by the following characters: left side of periandrium with a bifurcate process medially; left-ventral margin with a reversed process and right-ventral margin with a long process apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
